## Sidebar System (`src/components/sidebar/`)

### Sidebar

**Location:** `src/components/sidebar/Sidebar.tsx`

**Purpose:** Sliding sidebar panel with animations, stacking support, and scroll lock management.

**Props:**

```typescript
type PropsT = {
  children: ReactNode; // Sidebar content
  className?: string;
  headerActions?: ReactNode; // Additional header buttons
  name: SidebarNameE; // Sidebar identifier
  onBack?: () => void; // Back button handler
  onClose?: () => void; // Close callback
  title?: string; // Sidebar title
  size?: SidebarSizeE; // REGULAR or other sizes
};
```

**Key Features:**

- Renders via React Portal to `#sidebar_portal`
- Subscribes to global sidebar state
- Supports stacking (multiple sidebars open)
- Graceful closing animations via `deleted` flag
- Automatically closes on unmount
- Closes on backdrop click
- Scroll lock for REGULAR size (prevents body scroll)
- Back button support
- Header actions area
- Calls `sidebarService.finalizeClose()` after animation ends

**Usage Example:**

```typescript
import Sidebar from 'Components/sidebar/Sidebar';
import { SidebarNameE } from 'Components/sidebar/types/SidebarNameE';
import { SidebarSizeE } from 'Components/sidebar/types/SidebarSizeE';

// Sidebar component
const EditBudgetSidebar = () => {
  const sidebars = useGlobalValue(GlobalStoreFieldE.SIDEBAR);
  const props = sidebars.find(s => s.name === SidebarNameE.EDIT_BUDGET)?.props;

  if (!props) return null;

  return (
    <Sidebar
      name={SidebarNameE.EDIT_BUDGET}
      title="Edit Budget"
      size={SidebarSizeE.REGULAR}
      onClose={() => console.log('Closed')}
    >
      <BudgetForm budgetId={props.budgetId} />
    </Sidebar>
  );
};

// Open from anywhere
import { sidebarService } from 'Services/sidebarService';
sidebarService.openFirst(SidebarNameE.EDIT_BUDGET, { budgetId: 'uuid' });
```

**Dependencies:** `sidebarService`, `scrollLockService`, `useGlobalValue`, `createPortal`

**Related Files:**

- `SidebarNameE.ts` - Enum of sidebar names
- `SidebarPropsT.ts` - Type-safe props for each sidebar
- `SidebarSizeE.ts` - Sidebar size variants
- `SidebarLayout.tsx` - Layout wrapper for sidebar content

