## Component Patterns

### 1. Form Integration Pattern

Components that integrate with react-hook-form:

```typescript
import { useFormContext, useController } from 'react-hook-form';

const MyFormComponent = ({ name }: { name: string }) => {
  const { control } = useFormContext();
  const { field, fieldState: { error } } = useController({
    name,
    control,
    rules: { required: 'Required' }
  });

  return (
    <div>
      <input {...field} />
      {error && <span>{error.message}</span>}
    </div>
  );
};
```

### 2. Global State Subscription Pattern

Components that read from global state:

```typescript
import { useGlobalValue } from 'Shared/store/useGlobalValue';
import { GlobalStoreFieldE } from 'Shared/types/GlobalStoreFieldE';

const MyComponent = () => {
  const sidebars = useGlobalValue(GlobalStoreFieldE.SIDEBAR);

  return <div>{sidebars.length} open</div>;
};
```

### 3. Service-Managed UI Pattern

Components managed by services (modals, sidebars):

```typescript
// Component definition
const MySidebar = () => {
  const sidebars = useGlobalValue(GlobalStoreFieldE.SIDEBAR);
  const props = sidebars.find(s => s.name === SidebarNameE.MY_SIDEBAR)?.props;

  if (!props) return null;

  return (
    <Sidebar name={SidebarNameE.MY_SIDEBAR} title="Title">
      Content
    </Sidebar>
  );
};

// Usage - open from anywhere
sidebarService.openFirst(SidebarNameE.MY_SIDEBAR, { id: 'uuid' });
```

### 4. Portal Pattern

Components that render outside their parent DOM hierarchy:

```typescript
import { createPortal } from 'react-dom';

const container = document.getElementById('portal_root');

const MyPortalComponent = () => {
  return createPortal(
    <div>Portal Content</div>,
    container!,
    'unique-key'
  );
};
```

